<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-data-shapes">
  <title>Data Shapes</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section covers the concept of data shapes, including wide and long formats, and how to reshape data for different purposes.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Understand different data shapes (wide vs long format)</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Learn when to use different data formats</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Master techniques for reshaping data</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-wide-vs-long">
    <title>Wide vs Long Format</title>
    <p>
      Wide format has one row per subject with multiple columns for different measurements. Long format has multiple rows per subject with a single measurement column.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-reshaping-data">
    <title>Reshaping Data</title>
    <p>
      Different analyses and visualisations require different data shapes. Learning to reshape data between formats is an essential skill.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
